<style>
  .header__desktop {
    height: 70px;
  }

  .header__mobile {
    height: 60px;
  }

  /* A11y fix 2026-04-28 — footer accordion triggers were <p> with
     aria-controls/aria-haspopup/aria-expanded, which Lighthouse flagged
     as 'aria-allowed-attr' violation (those ARIA attrs require <button>
     or <a>). Changed sections/footer.liquid to <button type="button">.
     This rule resets browser button defaults so .footer__title still
     looks like the previous <p> styling: full-width text-aligned-left,
     transparent background, no border (the .footer__title rule already
     defines border-bottom), no extra padding from button defaults,
     inherits font from parent. */
  button.footer__title {
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0;
    padding: 0 0 10px;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    text-align: left;
    width: 100%;
    font: inherit;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: inherit;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: block;
    font-weight: var(---font-weight-accent-bold);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  button.footer__title:focus { outline: 2px solid var(--secondary); outline-offset: 2px; }

  /* CLS fix 2026-04-28 — Judge.me 'Verified by' logo image is rendered
     by app HTML without explicit width/height attributes. PSI flagged
     it as "Media element lacking an explicit size" causing layout
     shifts where the .jdgm-medals-wrapper appears (PDP footer +
     /reviews page). Reserving the rendered dimensions (125x24 per
     Lighthouse boundingRect) prevents the shift. Aspect ratio also
     declared so width: 100% containers compute height correctly. */
  .jdgm-verified-by__image {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 125px;
    height: 24px;
  }
  .jdgm-verified-by__image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
    aspect-ratio: 125 / 24;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-04-28 — Shop Sheriff PWA app injects #pwa-modal into the
     page body when it decides to prompt for "Install our app". Without
     position constraints, the modal pushes all subsequent in-flow content
     down — causing massive CLS. Real-shopper RUM data attributed 341
     poor-rated CLS events to #pwa-modal across the worst-performing
     pages in 14 days (per GA4 web-vitals-reporter pipeline + GSC's
     CrUX field data: dandruff-control collection at 0.29, blog/low-
     porosity at 0.54, blog/best-hair-color at 0.53, kerastase-blond-
     absolu PDP at 0.32, azta-urban-salon-service-menu at 0.30 mobile).

     Fix: force the modal to position: fixed (overlay, not in-flow) +
     contain: layout (its size changes don't affect siblings). The modal
     can still appear and serve its "Install our PWA" purpose — it just
     can't shift content around it.

     Selectors target the modal element itself + likely backdrop sibling.
     `!important` because Shop Sheriff's own CSS may set position absolute
     or static; we need to win specificity battles against external CSS.

     2026-05-01 escalation: position:fixed rule shipped 2026-04-28 was
     ineffective — GA4 #pwa-modal CLS stayed at ~2,127 events/7d for 3 days.
     Root cause found by inspecting Shop Sheriff main.js: their pwaSlideIn
     keyframes animate `top: -100%` → `top: 0` (animating the `top` property
     itself, not transform). Animating `top` triggers layout on every frame,
     so position:fixed didn't help. Fix: display:none prevents the element
     from rendering, so the animation never runs. Modal also has multiple
     non-installprompt triggers (displayAlways, timeOnPage), so JS-side
     event suppression alone wouldn't catch all paths. PWA install via
     Chrome address bar still works (manifest.json preserved in
     shop-sheriff-pwa.liquid). Re-measure GA4 in 24h post-ship. */
  #pwa-modal,
  [id^="pwa-modal"],
  [class*="pwa-modal"] {
    display: none !important;
    position: fixed !important;
    z-index: 9999 !important;
    contain: layout !important;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-04-29 — Blog article body images come from Shopify's
     rich-text editor, which doesn't add width/height attributes. Without
     dimensions, browsers can't reserve space → image loads → all content
     below shifts down → catastrophic CLS.

     Real-shopper RUM data (GA4 web-vitals last 7 days) showed 4 of the
     top 5 worst CLS pages were blog posts:
       /blogs/hair-education/rebonding-vs-keratin-treatment   54.9% poor
       /blogs/product-spotlight/lockdown-lab-purple-shampoos  51.9% poor
       /blogs/product-spotlight/15-top-sulfate-free-shampoos  49.2% poor (n=392)
       /blogs/tousled-online-magazine/how-to-hide-gray-hair   47.1% poor

     Fix strategy:
     1. `aspect-ratio: auto 16 / 9` — when intrinsic ratio is unknown
        (image hasn't loaded yet), fall back to 16:9 (most blog photos
        are landscape). When intrinsic ratio becomes available, browser
        switches to it. This pre-reserves vertical space at first paint.
     2. `width: 100%` paired with the aspect-ratio so the browser can
        compute height upfront from container width.
     3. `height: auto` ensures intrinsic ratio wins once image loads,
        even if intrinsic differs from 16:9.
     4. `max-width: 100%` prevents oversized images overflowing.
     5. `display: block` prevents baseline-aligned shifts from inline imgs.
     6. Background placeholder color so the reserved area is visible
        instead of empty white.

     Selector targets `.blog__article__content` (full article page) and
     all `.rte` content (blog list/preview cards too). Limited to images
     that DON'T already have width+height attrs (skips already-sized
     images so the rule doesn't accidentally regress them).

     Caveat: portrait images will appear as 16:9 first then snap to
     their portrait ratio when loaded — still better than 0px → full
     height jump. For perfect fix, would need server-side image
     dimension parsing in Liquid (article.content is HTML string, no
     direct Image objects). Acceptable trade-off given the 49–55% poor
     baseline. */
  .blog__article__content img,
  .rte img {
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }
  .blog__article__content img:not([width]):not([height]),
  .rte img:not([width]):not([height]) {
    aspect-ratio: auto 16 / 9;
    width: 100%;
    background: #f4f6f8;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-04-29 — Judge.me medals wrapper starts as `.jdgm-hidden`
     (display: none) in the initial HTML and gets revealed by Judge.me's
     loader.js once badges hydrate. The reveal grows the wrapper from 0
     to ~80px tall, pushing all subsequent in-flow content down → CLS.

     Real-shopper RUM showed /products/wella-professionals-koleston-
     perfect-ppd-free 49.1% poor CLS (n=116 events). Wella PDP image
     gallery is dimensioned correctly (width=1180 height=1180), so the
     remaining CLS source is the medals wrapper appearing post-load.
     Same pattern likely affects all PDPs with Judge.me reviews snippet.

     Fix: while .jdgm-hidden is applied, override display to block but
     keep visibility: hidden so the element occupies its eventual height
     without showing content. min-height: 80px reserves the typical
     rendered height of 5 badges in a row. contain: layout prevents
     residual size variance from cascading to siblings. When Judge.me
     removes .jdgm-hidden, the badges become visible in the same space.

     Caveat: if Judge.me's JS gates hydration on display: none → display:
     block transition, this override could break their logic. Loader.js
     v490 (audited 2026-04-27 per beads memory) gates on
     .jdgm-preview-badge presence, not display state, so the override
     should be safe. Revert this rule if medals stop appearing. */
  .jdgm-medals-wrapper.jdgm-hidden {
    display: block !important;
    visibility: hidden !important;
    min-height: 80px;
    contain: layout;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 T2 / 2026-05-02 1pi update — Cart page:
     #freegifts-main-page-container. Initial T2 fix reserved 80px (one gift
     row). Post-fix GA4 still shows 141 poor-CLS events/7d on the outer cart
     wrapper (div.wrapper.pt2.pb4). When active offers show 2 gift rows, the
     injected height is ~160px — overflowing the 80px reservation and shifting
     all cart items below. Increased to 160px (2 gift rows: each row ~70px +
     ~10px header/spacing). The 160px blank gap when no gifts are active is
     the accepted trade-off. contain:layout unchanged. */
  #freegifts-main-page-container {
    min-height: 160px;
    contain: layout;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 T8 — PDP Flickity media thumbs:
     div.media__thumb__wrapper.flickity-enabled.is-draggable is the GA4
     debug_target for 36 poor-CLS events in 7d on PDP pages. Before Flickity
     initializes, the wrapper has no explicit height — its height comes from
     the inline-block .media__thumb items (each 60px + 15px vertical margins
     = ~75px rendered). When Flickity fires, it restructures the wrapper DOM
     and briefly collapses the strip before re-measuring.

     Fix: set min-height on the wrapper to the typical rendered height
     (80px = 60px thumb + 10px top margin + 5px bottom margin + 5px buffer).
     contain:layout prevents internal Flickity reflows from cascading.
     overflow:hidden prevents any overflow during Flickity's brief transition. */
  .media__thumb__wrapper {
    min-height: 80px;
    contain: layout;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 T9 — Header CLS:
     GA4 debug_target theme__header recorded 88 poor-CLS events in 7d.
     Two causes:

     1. Announcement bar: the ticker JS (announcement__scale ticker--unloaded
        → loaded) and the Flickity slider init both fire after DOM parse,
        potentially causing the .announcement__wrapper height to briefly
        change. The announcement section renders before the header in DOM;
        any height change there can affect the absolute-positioned header's
        visual position at the top of the page.

     2. LoyaltyLion .points-box: for logged-in users, two data-lion-points
        spans inside .header__desktop start empty then get injected with the
        points balance by LoyaltyLion's SDK. The injection can cause the
        account navlink to reflow internally.

     Fix 1: min-height on .announcement__wrapper prevents the bar from
     collapsing to 0 during ticker initialization. 36px is the typical
     rendered height of a single-line announcement bar (font-size ~14px
     + ~22px vertical padding from .announcement__bar).

     Fix 2: .points-box gets height: 0 / overflow: hidden for logged-out
     users (no .is-loggedin → spans never get display:block from theme.css
     line 15667). For logged-in users it stays block. contain:layout on
     .points-box prevents the injection from reflowing sibling nav items. */
  .announcement__wrapper {
    min-height: 36px;
  }

  .points-box {
    contain: layout;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 e4a-α — PDP store availability widget:
     .product__pickup contains [data-store-availability-container], an empty
     div in the Liquid that Zapiet's app embed populates with store pickup
     availability after JS loads. The div grows 0px → ~60px when Zapiet
     fires, shifting the footer and any below-fold content. Same injection
     pattern as #freegifts-main-page-container (fixed earlier today).

     Fix: reserve 64px (typical height of a single store row: store name
     ~20px + status ~20px + 4px gap + 20px vertical padding). contain:layout
     isolates internal Zapiet DOM mutations from cascading to siblings.
     The gap when no stores match the variant is an acceptable white-space
     trade-off vs. a layout shift on every PDP pageload. */
  .product__pickup {
    min-height: 64px;
    contain: layout;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 e4a-β — PDP Flickity main gallery height animation:
     .product__slides .flickity-viewport has `transition: height 0.4s` in
     theme.css line 14885. This animated height transition fires whenever
     Flickity adjusts viewport height — including during init on pages where
     the first-slide aspect-ratio and --default-ratio match (so net shift is
     0), the 400ms animation still triggers continuous layout recalc that
     browsers can record as micro-shifts.

     Fix: override the transition to `none` for the main product gallery only.
     The thumbnail strip (.media__thumb__wrapper) already has contain:layout
     (T8 fix) and doesn't need this. Disabling the transition means height
     changes snap immediately — one discrete event rather than 400ms of
     animated shifts. The visual experience is unchanged because the aspect-
     ratio pre-reservation (--default-ratio inline style on .product__slides)
     means the viewport should not need to change height at all on init for
     most products. */
  .product__slides .flickity-viewport {
    transition: none !important;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-01 7fz — Reamaze chat widget label:
     GA4 debug_target #reamaze-widget-label recorded 14 poor-CLS events in 7d
     (7fz attribution query). The Reamaze widget label animates from off-screen
     into its bottom-right corner position after JS loads. The animate-in shifts
     any in-flow content it's adjacent to before settling as position:fixed.

     Fix: force the label to position:fixed at all times so it never participates
     in document flow. The widget still appears and functions — it just can't
     shift content around it. contain:layout isolates any internal re-renders. */
  #reamaze-widget-label,
  [id^="reamaze-widget"] {
    position: fixed !important;
    contain: layout !important;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-02 fan — PDP product price column:
     GA4 debug_target div.grid__item.medium-up--one-half logged 251 poor-CLS
     events/7d across all PDPs (Wella all-shades worst at 44 events, 52% poor).
     Root cause: bss-b2b-product-vat.liquid inlines a <style> that hides
     .shopify-section .product__price with display:none before BSS B2B JS
     reveals the correct price. This collapses .product__price__wrap from its
     rendered height (~44px for price text + padding) to 0, then BSS JS sets
     display:block → the price area re-expands → shifts variant selector, ATC
     button, and all content below.

     Fix: reserve 44px on .product__price__wrap so the price row never
     collapses to 0. contain:layout prevents internal price changes (sale
     badges, strikethrough compare-at price) from cascading to siblings.
     The 44px reservation is visible as a blank strip ONLY for users who load
     the page before BSS B2B JS fires (sub-300ms window). Acceptable vs.
     251 poor-CLS events/7d. */
  .product__price__wrap {
    min-height: 44px;
    contain: layout;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-02 1pi-b — Cart page recently-viewed section:
     sections/section-recent-products.liquid renders with style="display:none"
     on the products container. JS populates from localStorage then removes
     display:none. Section grows from 0 → ~360px (6 product cards × ~60px
     row height) pushing site footer down. Footer is below-fold so CLS impact
     is low, but still recorded in GA4. Reserve 300px (minimum 4 products ×
     ~75px each) to prevent the grow-from-zero shift. */
  .section-recent.recent__container {
    min-height: 300px;
    contain: layout;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-02 e4a-γ — Klaviyo body-injected signup modal:
     PSI filmstrip frame 8 on serioxyl PDP shows the Klaviyo signup modal
     appearing mid-load and pushing PDP content. Klaviyo's runtime CSS
     sets the modal to position:fixed once their stylesheet hydrates, but
     between when the modal HTML is appended to <body> and when their CSS
     loads, the modal briefly occupies document flow as a body child →
     shifts every in-flow sibling below it.

     Confirmed safe: `grep -rn "klaviyo-form" sections/ snippets/` returns
     zero inline embeds — Klaviyo at HairMNL is exclusively the body-level
     modal popup injected by the Klaviyo Shopify App Embed. The selector
     uses `body > ...` so any future inline form embedded inside a section
     container is unaffected. Forcing position:fixed in our <head> CSS
     wins because <head> parses before Klaviyo's loader script downloads.

     Class patterns covered:
     - `klaviyo-form-*` — Klaviyo's standard modal form ID class
     - `kl-private-reset-css-*` — Klaviyo's css-reset wrapper (random suffix)
     - `[data-testid^="klaviyo-form"]` — newer Klaviyo SDK builds

     Caveat: this rule will break any Klaviyo embed form rendered as a
     direct <body> child (atypical — embeds normally live inside section
     containers). Revert if signup CTAs stop appearing inline anywhere. */
  body > [class*="klaviyo-form"],
  body > div[class*="kl-private-reset-css"],
  body > [data-testid^="klaviyo-form"] {
    position: fixed !important;
    z-index: 9999 !important;
    contain: layout !important;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-02 e4a-δ — LoyaltyLion body-injected notification/popup:
     LoyaltyLion's "Sign up for HairMNL Rewards to get a Php100 voucher"
     notification bar and any LL overlay popup are injected as direct body
     children by their SDK loader (sdk.loyaltylion.net/static/2/loader.js,
     dns-prefetched at theme.liquid:87). Same lifecycle gap as Klaviyo —
     SDK appends the notification HTML before its own stylesheet sets
     position:fixed, so it briefly renders in flow.

     Selector targets only body-level descendants:
     - `[id^="lion-"]` — LL's standard ID prefix on overlay/notification els
     - `[class*="ll-notification"]` / `[class*="ll-popup"]` — LL legacy markup
     - `[class*="lion-overlay"]` — LL modal backdrop

     The `.lion-points-box` element is NOT body-level (it lives inside
     .header__desktop nav, theme.liquid header section), so `body > ...`
     scoping naturally excludes it — the T9 header CLS fix at
     css-overrides.liquid:235 handles that one in-flow.

     Caveat: any future LL embed widget rendered as direct body child
     (atypical for LL — they place inline widgets via merchant-supplied
     containers like `<div data-loyaltylion></div>`) would break. */
  body > [id^="lion-"],
  body > [class*="ll-notification"],
  body > [class*="ll-popup"],
  body > [class*="lion-overlay"] {
    position: fixed !important;
    contain: layout !important;
  }

  /* CLS fix 2026-05-04 0u4 — Booster EU Cookie Bar / Nova GDPR cookie banner:
     The Nova EU Cookie Bar GDPR app embed (settings_data.json: nova-eu-cookie-bar-gdpr,
     confirmed active) uses the cookieconsent library which:
     1. Injects inline <style> into <head> at runtime via createElement
     2. Creates .cc-window.cc-banner DOM (position:fixed in its own CSS)
     Between step 1 and step 2 the element can briefly render in document
     flow — same lifecycle gap as Klaviyo/LoyaltyLion above. Pre-loading
     position:fixed in our <head> CSS wins the race because custom-theme.css
     and css-overrides.liquid parse before any app script downloads.

     Banner is bottom-aligned on desktop and mobile:
     - .cc-window — base cookieconsent window class (all variants)
     - .cc-window.cc-banner — the bottom-bar variant shown on HairMNL
     bottom/left/right are explicit so the banner stays visible in its
     correct position even if the cookieconsent CSS loads late or fails.

     contain:layout prevents the fixed element's size/position from
     affecting surrounding in-flow elements (belt-and-suspenders with
     position:fixed, but required for accurate CLS attribution).

     Caveat: if Nova/Booster changes its DOM class naming, this rule
     becomes a no-op (harmless — falls back to their own CSS). */
  .cc-window,
  .cc-window.cc-banner {
    position: fixed !important;
    bottom: 0 !important;
    left: 0 !important;
    right: 0 !important;
    contain: layout !important;
  }
</style>